# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Test catalog
#
# Three parallel associative arrays keyed by test-function name:
#   _TEST_KIND        — category tag (see below)
#   _TEST_DESTRUCTIVE — true if the test can modify or delete live data;
#                       these are skipped when --skip-e2e is passed
#   _TEST_REQUIRES    — comma-separated capabilities that must be
#                       present; test is skipped if any are unmet
#
# Kind tags:
#   cli    — validates flags/arguments; no live services needed
#   scan   — security scanner (Trivy, Grype)
#   advise — advisory only: Dive, kcov; never block the run
#   switch — tests behavioral flags; no live AWS or network needed
#   aws    — requires S3_BUCKET_NAME + AWS credentials
#   cron   — tests scheduler behavior inside the container
#
# Capability requirements (values in _TEST_REQUIRES):
#   aws    — S3_BUCKET_NAME set + at least one AWS credential source
#   host   — HOST env var set (live target reachable)
#
# Test function bodies live in test/staging-hooks.sh.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
